thread.title: Greek PM wins parliament backing for bailout reforms package
thread.title_full: Greek PM wins parliament backing for bailout reforms package | Reuters

author: Reuters
title: Greek PM wins parliament backing for bailout reforms package
text:
ATHENS, July 23 Greek Prime Minister Alexis Tsipras faced down a revolt by rebels in his leftists Syriza party to win parliament's backing on Thursday for a second package of reforms required to start talks on a financial rescue deal.
The bill - containing judicial and banking reforms - easily passed with the support of 230 lawmakers in the 300-seat parliament thanks to the support of pro-euro opposition parties.
But 36 out of 149 deputies from his Syriza party voted against the overall bill or abstained - less than the rebellion by 39 deputies in last week's vote on an initial set of reforms.
(Reporting Renee Maltezou, Lefteris Papadimas and Karolina Tagaris, Writing by Deepa Babington)
